history.content:
It's not because of time conflicts. That message shows up because ... well, because Oracle created the enrollment management system campus bought. 

It's because the class is full and has a waitlist.

I'm trying to get into EECS149 from IND ENG 192 but I got this message saying my swap request didn't go through:

You have NOT been enrolled from the wait list into the following class:

Term: 2019 Fall

Class: EECS   149 

Section: 001

Reason: Time conflict with another section.

As neither class allows time conflict enrollments, you will remain on the waitlist unless or until you resolve the time conflict.

What I don't get is that on calcentral, 149 states that it allows for time conflicts. Does anyone know what might be up?
history.subject: Swap conflict didn't go through even though class allows for it?
